article.headline: UCF 73, Stetson 60
article.story: ORLANDO, Fla. (AP) -- Jermaine Taylor had 21 points to pave the way for Central Florida to defeat in-state rival Stetson 73-60 on Saturday night. The Golden Knights stretched their winning streak over the Hatters to 10 games. UCF (2-0) was 1-for-9 from beyond the arc against Stetson (1-3). However, the Golden Knights were tenacious in the paint, outscoring the Hatters 46-18, and held a 48-23 rebounding margin. Although UCF dominated the glass in the first half, 28-10, both teams suffered from poor shooting early in the game. It took the Golden Knights 4:43 until they made their first field goal, while Stetson had a 5:32 span in which it failed to make a bucket. Garfield Blair finished with 18 points for Stetson and Kris Thomas added 17.
